  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether antenatal model in vaginosis are effective
      in preventing vaginal infection and preterm delivery
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The standard antenatal care nowadays can not answer for preterm delivery problems. Thus,
      comprehensive and proactive approach is needed for preventing preterm delivery. This
      antenatal model is consisted of midwife training, early detection of bacterial vaginosis,
      pregnant women campaign and self administered pH check
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
